\title{Ordered pairs}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[paul-r-halmos]] [[halmos-1974-naive]] Ch.6}
\MML{tarski}{def 5}{K4}

\p{Let #{x} and #{y} be objects. We define the \define{Ordered Pair} to be the object #{(x,y) = \{\{x\},\{x,y\}\}}.}

\rmk{A better definition would be #{(x,y)=\{\{0,x\},\{1,y\}\}} because then the [[nst-000O]] coincides with the [[nst-002E]] when #{I=\{0,1\}} is the indexing set.}